                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13032693" author="mortazavi" created="Thu, 12 May 2011 22:35:51 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Also, in the same place:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/viewvc/db/derby/code/trunk/java/testing/README.htm?view=co&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/viewvc/db/derby/code/trunk/java/testing/README.htm?view=co&lt;/a&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;there seems to be a spurious quotation mark in class path defined in section 2.1:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;   set CLASSPATH=&quot;$ &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And on Mac&apos;s default bash shell, I used &quot;export&quot; instead of &quot;set&quot; and &quot;source&quot;-ing was necessary.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13032700" author="mortazavi" created="Thu, 12 May 2011 22:52:26 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I did notice that tstjardir is where jakarta-oro and junit are installed. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13032704" author="mortazavi" created="Thu, 12 May 2011 23:00:58 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;It would be nice to know how to direct the logs into a directory other than from where the tests are being run. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(I ran derbylang tests with no failures reported, following the rest of the instructions. So, Rick is right, they seem to be alright, perhaps modulo some of the improvements suggested above.)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13032977" author="knutanders" created="Fri, 13 May 2011 13:05:32 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;The attached patch makes the following changes:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) Add a description of the jardir and tstjardir convenience variables.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2) Add a closing double quote in the set CLASSPATH statement.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;3) Simplify the suggested CLASSPATH by removing jar files that will be pulled in automatically by derbyrun.jar.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I didn&apos;t change &quot;set&quot; to &quot;export&quot; as I expect that to differ from shell to shell. (I have no idea which shell uses &quot;set&quot; instead of &quot;export&quot; or &quot;setenv&quot;, but I guess it&apos;s good enough as an example.)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Committed revision 1102688.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13032981" author="knutanders" created="Fri, 13 May 2011 13:17:32 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt; It would be nice to know how to direct the logs into a directory other than from where the tests are being run.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t think there is any way to do this currently. It might be useful functionality, but this is an old test framework that we&apos;re trying to move away from in favour of JUnit, so I doubt that anyone will put much effort into improving the framework itself going forward. There&apos;s still a long way to go before we can retire the old framework for good, though...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13685239" author="knutanders" created="Mon, 17 Jun 2013 10:19:26 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;bulk update&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; Close all resolved issues that haven&apos;t been updated for more than one year.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
